ame\": \"What medical treatments can help with constipation?\",\n    \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n      \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n      \"text\": \"Constipation may resolve on its own without the need for prescription treatment. However, laxatives can improve symptoms in the short term.\nIt is best to take laxatives for no more than a week at a time. If a person needs to use laxatives for more than a week, it is possible that they may need to treat an underlying condition that is causing constipation.\"\n    }\n  },{\n    \"@type\": \"Question\",\n    \"name\": \"Can natural remedies help treat constipation?\",\n    \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n      \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n      \"text\": \"Some natural remedies may help a person relieve constipation. They include:\ngetting enough dietary fiber, aiming for around 22–34 grams per day\ndrinking enough water\ngetting enough regular physical activity or exercise\nchoosing the same time each day to try and have a bowel movement\"\n    }\n  },{\n    \"@type\": \"Question\",\n    \"name\": \"What are the possible complications of constipation?\",\n    \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n      \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n      \"text\": \"Constipation may cause complications if it persists or if it is a symptom of a more serious underlying condition.\nDamage that can arise as a result of constipation includes:\nhemorrhoids or piles, which are swollen, inflamed blood vessels in the anus\nrectal bleeding after straining\nbowel incontinence\nanal fissure, which is a small tear around the anus\nfecal impaction, which occurs when dried stool stops moving and collects in the rectum and anus, potentially leading to a mechanical obstruction\"\n    }\n  },{\n    \"@type\": \"Question\",\n    \"name\": \"How do I get rid of constipation fast?\",\n    \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n      \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n      \"text\": \"Laxatives may help relieve constipation quickly. Stimulant laxatives take approximately 6–12 hours to work.\"\n    }\n  },{\n    \"@type\": \"Question\",\n    \"name\": \"What makes constipation go away?\",\n    \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n      \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n      \"text\": \"Laxatives can help make constipation go away. However, if symptoms do not respond to laxatives, then a person may require treatments for an underlying cause. Home remedies such as increasing dietary fiber intake and drinking enough water can help regulate bowel movements.\"\n    }\n  }]\n}\n"},{"tagName":"h3","source":"How do I get rid of constipation fast?"},{"tagName":"p","source":"Laxatives may help relieve constipation quickly. Stimulant laxatives take approximately \u003ca rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/laxatives/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003e6–12 hours\u003c/a\u003e to work."},{"tagName":"h3","source":"What makes constipation go away?"},{"tagName":"p","source":"Laxatives can help make constipation go away. However, if symptoms do not respond to laxatives, then a person may require treatments for an underlying cause. Home remedies such as increasing dietary fiber intake and drinking enough water can help regulate bowel movements."}]},{"id":"Learn-more","isCollapsable":false,"header":["Learn more"],"body":[{"tagName":"ul","source":"\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/best-medication-for-constipation\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eWhat is the best medication for constipation?\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/chronic-constipation\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eWhat to know about chronic constipation\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150322\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eWhat to know about constipation\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/types-of-constipation\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eWhat to 